cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) and network virtualization, which are both topics related to computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the architecture and execution platform of SDN hypervisors, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the isolation and abstraction features of SDN hypervisors, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
